reviewText: Old Bogart. But one step closer to making my collection complete
I love Bogie, he is great in any movie.

Acting was amazing.  But it did not appear to be digitally remastered, and on the package it says, "color," and it is definitely black & white!!  We did enjoy the movie.  Great to see such a young Humphrey Bogart.

Wasn't his best. They featured more of the lesser known actors and Bogart was not really a main character. I was disappointed with the film because it was awfully slow. Bogart IS good in this, but his presence in the film was minimal. I felt ripped off personally and didn't really care for this one. The picture quality is only okay. Otherwise save your money to watch more of a solid presence of Bogart.
if its digitally remastered then I am a ?. also its not in colour as stated on back cover .

I'm a huge Bogart fan,  so this movie was a must.  The movie itself was amazing.  Truly a great bogart film; that being said the transfer wasn't the best.  The volume and picture wasn't quite as crisp as i would like.  But considering this is the only means to get this particular movie i would say it was worth it.
No such thing as a bad Bogart movie.
THE DVD WAS OF GOOD QUALITY.  The movie had been also  released under the name MIDNIGHT and Bogart was only listed in a supporting role.
